parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The detachment of the rear spoiler can cause damage to the vehicle, surrounding property, and potentially lead to accidents. It can also obstruct the rearview camera, compromising the driver's visibility.
symptoms: The rear spoiler detaches while driving
the rear spoiler is loose or hanging
the rear spoiler is missing a panel
the rear spoiler hits other vehicles or objects.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fuel System Failure - Gasoline Odor and Leaks
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel system can cause gasoline odors and leaks, which can lead to accidents, fires, or explosions, posing a significant risk to the driver and passengers.
symptoms: Strong gasoline odor inside and outside the vehicle

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the fuel gauge can cause the driver to run out of fuel, leading to accidents, strandings, or other safety issues.
symptoms: fuel gauge shows warnings of low fuel levels even when the tank is full

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the cooling system can cause engine overheating, leading to serious misfires, engine damage, and potentially catastrophic consequences.
symptoms: Antifreeze levels constantly dropping with no visual leaks

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the timing chain can cause serious engine damage, leading to catastrophic consequences, including engine seizure and failure.
The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to a loss of power steering and brakes, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: loss of power steering and brakes
and inability to start the vehicle again.
